<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3777924>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Omanocossonus sabulosus sp. nov., male genitalia: A—aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view; B—male sternite 9 (spiculum gastrale); C—aedeagus, upper sclerite, D—tegmen; and female genitals: E—female sternite 8 (spiculum ventrale); F—ovipositor; G—rectal loop; H—spermatheca. Scales bars: 0.2 mm (A–C, D–H), and 0.05 mm (C)." ;
